	abstract = {This paper describes a design method for a 446 Mb/s optical repeater with four kinds of monolithic integrated circuits. It is concerned with circuit division, optical receiver and timing amplifier design methods. The repeater circuit is divided based on maximum allowable again and power consumption. Allowable gain determined by IC package crosstalk characteristics at 400 MHz transmission band is presented. Allowable maximum power consumption of 1w/chip is determined. Effective amplification bandwidth adjustment methods for the optical receiver and the d. c. drift control (DCFB) system design method, specific in the d. c. coupled monolithic integrated optical receiver, are described. A design method for the small-phase-shift timing amplifier is proposed. This is a circuit parameter optimizing method which monitors operating point dependence of small signal amplification bandwidth. A 446Mbit/s submerged optical repeater has been developed using these design methods.},
